#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:17
msgid "We will now briefly describe some of the database tables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:20
msgid "db_dbnode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:21
msgid "This table contains the information about all the Node instances stored in AiiDA. Since the Node class has various sub-classes, there is a column (named ``type``) at the ``db_dbnode`` table that indicates the type of the node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:25
msgid "Other columns are the ``ctime`` and ``mtime`` that correspond to the creation time and the modification time of the node. There are foreign keys that link this table with the ``db_dbcomputer`` and the ``db_dbuser`` tables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:29
msgid "It is also worth noting the ``attributes`` and ``extras`` columns that are of type JSONB. This type allows to store directly JSON snippets in such columns while they can be indexed for fast searching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:34
msgid "db_dbuser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:35
msgid "The ``db_dbuser`` table contains user related information.  It is worth noting that the stored password column contained hashed information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:39
msgid "db_dblink"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:40
msgid "The AiiDA nodes are connected with links and form a graph. The links are stored in the ``db_dblink`` table. The columns of that table contain the name of the link, the id of the input & output nodes and the type of the node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:45
msgid "db_dbgroup & db_dbgroup_dbnodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:46
msgid "The nodes can be grouped into groups. In the ``db_dbgroup`` table contains information about the group like the name, the type and the description of the group. The nodes that are contained in the group are stored in ``db_dbgroup_dbnodes`` table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:52
msgid "db_dbcomment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/developer_guide/core/database_schema.rst:53
msgid "In the ``db_dbcomment`` table comments made by users to specific nodes are stored."
msgstr ""

